==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Agiotage
<hw>Ag"i*o*tage</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>agiotage</ets>, fr. <ets>agioter</ets> to practice stockjobbing,
fr. <ets>agio</ets>.]</ety> <def>Exchange business; also, stockjobbing;
the maneuvers of speculators to raise or lower the price of stocks or
public funds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Vanity and <qex>agiotage</qex> are to a Parisian the oxygen and
hydrogen of life.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>agism</ent>⟦br⟧
